    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the hotlines just feel so hollow. they tell me to hold on, but they don't live in this body. they don't know what it's like to have every single nerve ending screaming at you every second of every day. i'm not looking for a lecture or a phone number, i just... i keep thinking about how much more merciful it would be to just not be here anymore. to finally have that stillness. does that even sound crazy to say?",
